full_summary:
### Rental Vehicles Tender

**Title:** Rental Vehicles
**Reference Number:** PW-22-01010744
**Solicitation Number:** W8484-230340
**Publication Date:** 2022-10-20
**Tender Closing Date:** 2022-10-24T11:00:00

**Background and Objective:**
The Department of National Defence (DND) requires rental vehicles for personnel stationed in Atsugi, Japan from 04 Nov 22 to 21 Nov 22. This tender invitation seeks proposals from contractors to provide rental vehicles that meet the specified requirements.

**Task/Requirements:**
The contractor must provide the following types of rental vehicles: 4 x full-size sedans and 12 x passenger vans. Each vehicle must be in good condition, serviced, and inspected prior to delivery. The contractor must ensure that the vehicles are no more than four years old, have not exceeded 75,000 kilometers, and have the required features.

**Insurance and Liability:**
The contractor must provide collision damage waiver insurance at a flat rate. The contractor will be responsible for any losses or damages resulting from normal wear and tear, and the Canadian Armed Forces (CAF) will be responsible for any losses or damages resulting from negligence or carelessness of their personnel.

**Deliverables:**
The contractor must provide the following deliverables: rentals of the specified vehicles, assistance in processing traffic violations, and ensuring all relevant information is provided to the CAF point of contact.

**Responsibilities:**
The contractor will be responsible for providing vehicles with a minimum of one-quarter (¼) tank of fuel upon issuance and for accepting the vehicle to be returned with the same quantity of fuel. The contractor must provide a local point of contact and ensure that all documentation, including insurance for multiple drivers, is prepared and provided.

**CAF Responsibilities:**
The CAF will provide fuel for the vehicles while in use and ensure that each vehicle is returned with the same quantity and type of fuel.

**Notice and Closing Date:**
The notice for this tender was published on 2022-10-20, and the tender closing date is 2022-10-24T11:00:00. Proposals must be submitted electronically through the Canada Buys portal.

**Attachments:**
The tender package includes the following attachments:
* English version of the tender document
* French version of the tender document
* Contract identification
